{
  "texts": [
    "After long-coasting phases and prior to liquid transfer, the saturated fluid needs to be subcooled to avoid flow cavitation during transfer or re-ignition of the engine.",
    "Efficient cryocoolers are not available in the case of liquid hydrogen.",
    "Therefore, the cooling of liquid hydrogen is currently performed by pressure variation cycles 22.",
    "This tank propellant conditioning process involves depressurization followed by re-pressurization.",
    "The depressurization phase will remove thermal energy from the saturated liquid phase (pool cavitation in Fig. 1) and evaporate a part of the liquid, which leads to superheated conditions."
  ]
}